<p class="eyebrow">Calculator</p>
<h1>Calculate the workload, not the slogan.</h1>
<p class="lede">The calculator lets buyers model monthly usage and see every line item: minutes, messages, numbers, emergency service, lookups, AMD, recordings, and optional media features. Usage inputs stay in the browser.</p>
<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/pricing/">Open pricing</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/voiceml/migrate/">Migration guide</a>
</p>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="calculator-fields">
	<h2>Default inputs</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Voice</strong> — Inbound local minutes, outbound US-50 and Canada minutes, toll-free inbound minutes, AMD calls, recordings, conferences, streams, and transcriptions.</li>
		<li><strong>Messaging</strong> — SMS outbound, SMS inbound, MMS outbound, MMS inbound, carrier pass-through notes, and A2P 10DLC fees where applicable.</li>
		<li><strong>Numbers</strong> — Local numbers, toll-free numbers, emergency-service records, CNAM, and porting assumptions.</li>
		<li><strong>Competitor</strong> — Default to Twilio. Add other competitors only where reliable, source-dated data exists for the exact same unit.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="privacy">
	<h2>Privacy</h2>
	<p>Usage inputs stay in the browser. The calculator does not collect, transmit, or store customer workload data.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="assumptions">
	<h2>Assumptions</h2>
	<p>Every result shows the unit, VoiceTel rate, competitor source date, carrier-fee handling, and whether taxes, regulatory charges, discounts, or contract pricing are excluded.</p>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block">
	<h2>Need a modeled invoice?</h2>
	<p>For high-volume workloads, route planning and carrier fees matter. Bring an invoice and VoiceTel can build a detailed model from real usage.</p>
	<p class="hero-actions">
		<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact/">Request a pricing review</a>
	</p>
</aside>
